@andreoss @victornoel
Practical using IsEmpty class to create matcher in org.llorllale.cactoos.matchers;
TextIsEmpty
and then instead of using of new matcher:
 new Assertion<>( "The result text wasn't empty", new TextOf(input), new TextIs("") ).affirm();
Like here:
https://github.com/yegor256/cactoos/blob/master/src/test/java/org/cactoos/io/HeadInputStreamTest.java#L79
We would use:
        new Assertion<>( "The result text wasn't empty", new TextOf(input), new TextIsEmpty() ).affirm();
I think it is much more readable with using IsEmpty
